ENUGU – Governor Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi of Enugu State has assured corps members in the state of their safety. Ugwuanyi gave the assurance at the closing ceremony of 2019 Batch ‘C’ (Stream One) NYSC Orientation Course at the Permanent Orientation Camp, Awgu LGA, Enugu State. The governor said his administration was passionate about corps members’ security and had made adequate security arrangements for them wherever they were posted to serve. He also cautioned corps members serving in the state to desist from unauthorised journeys this festive period to reduce the chances of getting involved in road accidents. He further announced to the corps members that the state government would reward those who render excellent services to the state at the places of their primary assignments, assuring that the state would continue to give maximum support towards achieving the objectives of the NYSC scheme in the state.